                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001/12–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-02T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 2, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 2—5:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 1316. In accordance telCan 777, November 30, I today expressed to
                    President Li US Government’s views on question of possible resignation in
                    US.</p>
                <p>Li declared very definitely that he does not intend resign at all, that he is
                    returning to China after his US visit and that he is determined to hold his
                    present post. He added that Generalissimo will not reassume presidency and has
                    so stated to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
